description:
Hyde Park Lawyers is a firm based next to the Supreme Court of New South Wales. The firm's practice areas include Commercial Law, Property Law, Family Law, Criminal Defence, and Migration Law.  
 We are currently seeking to employ a PLT student to assist the principal solicitor. This position is on a part time basis with a minimum requirement of working 3 days per week. 
  About you  
 Duties will include, but not limited to: 
 
 Conducting legal research; 
 Draft correspondences； 
 Assisting in litigation matters; 
 Assisting in conveyancing matters; 
 Document and file management; 
 Preparing documents for delivery, scanning and post; and 
 Lodgement of documents at relevant governmental authorities. 
 
 You must possess the following qualities: 
 
 Good level of Mandarin is essential; 
 Be punctual and have excellent attention to detail; 
 Possess a can-do and proactive attitude; 
 Be able to work independently; and 
 Good communication skills both written and verbal 
 
 All cover letters and resumes must be addressed to  Mr. David Wang  and forwarded to   admin@hydeparklawyers.com.au   
 Please note that this position will on an unpaid basis. 
 Past work experience/internship at a private practice is preferred. 
 Only short-listed candidates will be contacted.

About the role  
 We are a thriving and dynamic law firm practicing primarily in family, criminal and civil litigation. We are searching for a paralegal to work closely with the Principal Lawyer and Senior Solicitor. The Principal is an accredited Independent Childrens Lawyer, on the specialist domestic violence panel, family law panel, cross examination panel, specialist criminal law panel. The firm has a solid stimulating, interesting and varied work inflow.  
 We are expanding rapidly and are searching for the right paralegal to assist our Principal and team.  
  Your main duties in this role will include: 
 
 Assisting lawyers and other staff members with any administrative duties including telephone attendance, invoicing, drafting cost agreements and receipts, itemised bills, diary management, arranging and scheduling appointments, client correspondences, all correspondences with third party stakeholders including lawyers, Courts and prosecutors, opening and closing files and all other administrative duties; 
 Drafting email, letter and general day to day correspondence; 
 Researching and drafting all Court related documents including  affidavits, submissions, orders; 
 Acting as a first point of contact: dealing with phone calls and clients; 
 Providing a high level of administrative and legal assistance including but not limited to creation and maintenance of files, photocopying, complying briefs, data entry and drafting correspondence. 
 Dictaphone typing; 
 Accounts and billing; 
 Attending various venues outside of the business premises to file documents with a Court or statutory body, etc as required. 
 Researching and assisting in preparing legal submissions and documents. 
 Preparing and filing various applications along with all required documents 
 
  Skills and experience  
  The Candidate  
 To be successful you MUST have: 
 
 Experience as a Paralegal or Legal Secretary ; 
 Demonstrated ability to meet competing deadlines and work under pressure; 
 Advanced MS office skills in particular Word and Excel; 
 Fast and accurate typing speed of 70+ WPM 
 Confidence to liaise with professionals at all levels; 
 Great organisational skills and a keen eye for detail; 
 Advanced skills and experience with Microsoft applications Word, Excel, and Outlook 
 Exceptional time management and multi-tasking skills including ability to prioritise tasks and competing deadlines; 
 Exceptional drafting skills and written work; 
 A demonstrated ability to work independently in a fast-paced environment and organise workload to meet tight deadlines. 
 
  Benefits and perks  
 Pay to commensurate with experience. 
 Please forward a covering letter of no more than 250 words together with your CV addressing the selection criteria.

We are a young and dynamic firm practising primarily in family and criminal law. We are searching for a lawyer to work closely with the Principal and senior solicitor. The Principal is an accredited Independent Childrens Lawyer, on the specialist domestic violence panel, family law panel, cross examination panel, specialist criminal law panel. The firm has a solid stimulating, interesting and varied work inflow.  
 We are expanding rapidly and are searching for the right person to assist our team. In return, the successful candidate will have the opportunity to grow and excel significantly in their legal career. We are open to fast-paced career progression and we will offer progression for the right candidate.  
  About the role  
  Key responsibilities include: 
 
 Being the right hand to the Principal Lawyer in a very busy and growing boutique practice; 
 Working closely with the Principal on complex Family/ Civil litigation law matters; 
 Working autonomously and taking active carriage of complex files; 
 Court attendance including hearings, mentions, directions hearings, conciliation conferences, mediations, interim hearings, and instructing counsel in final hearings; 
 Researching, drafting and managing Court documents including statement of claims, affidavits, orders, case outlines, balance sheets, financial statements and all family law related court documents; 
 Independently advising clients on family law matters including taking instructions, preparing letters of advice, general day to day correspondence and management of the file; 
 Preparing and reviewing disclosure documents. 
 
  Skills and experience  
 What you must bring: 
 
 1-2 years minimum PQE; 
 You will have carriage of matters in the Federal Circuit Court/ Family Court/ Local Court and you should be able to run files with minimal supervision; 
 Advanced Microsoft office skills, in particular excel and word; 
 Experience in appearing in Court including running hearings; 
 A "can-do" attitude and proactive approach in all aspects of  Family/Civil law practice; 
 A working knowledge of Family/Civil litigation law; 
 Exceptional drafting skills and written work; 
 Exceptional time management and multi-tasking skills including ability to prioritise tasks and competing deadlines; 
 A demonstrated ability to work independently in a fast-paced environment and organise workload to meet tight deadlines; 
 Strategic thinker with a pragmatic approach to complex matter research and client outcome focus; 
 Willingness and ability to complete administrative tasks when required; 
 Must be quick and efficient with handling of files; 
 Knowledge of PEXA and LEAP preferable but not essential. 
 
 We offer the opportunity to work in a firm where you will have the ability to manage your files independently, whilst also having the benefit of exposure to other areas of law.  
  We reward entrepreneurial thinking -  If you are someone that thinks outside the box, likes to be efficient and has innovative ideas, you will thrive here! 
 Please send your CV and covering letter addressing the criteria (of no more than 1 page) to  mona@elbabalawyers.com .  
 Pay to commensurate with experience.

Herald Legal is a busy law firm located in Sydney CBD. We are looking to recruit a talented and capable law clerk to join our team. Herald Legal offers a tremendous amount of invaluable experience and exposure to a wide range of legal matters within a variety of practice areas including: 
 
 Litigation; 
 Commercial and Corporate Law; 
 Family Law; 
 Criminal Law; 
 Migration Law; 
 Property Law 
 
 Your responsibilities will include but not limited to assisting our Solicitors with reviewing documents, undertaking legal drafting, court documents search and file management. 
 Applications must include a cover letter, CV and Legal degree transcript. Please send your applications to  hr@heraldlegal.com.au

Rebus Legal is a busy boutique law firm specializing in Family, Criminal, Civil, Traffic, and Migration Law matters. 
 We have worked hard to establish a great reputation, have a strong growing client base and we continue to expand. 
 We currently have four available voluntary positions at our offices in Victoria Park for  PLT / Law Students looking to gain experience in furtherance of your law degree. 
  The successful candidate will have:  
 
 Direct access to experienced practitioners ensuring that you will work alongside the best in developing your interpersonal and professional skills and experience; 
 Access to free parking onsite; 
 Possible opportunity for ongoing employment, given the growth plan of the practice; 
 Experience to gain a reference for any future employment applications. 
 
  To be successful in this role you must:  
 
 Have an excellent work ethic; 
 Possess excellent written and verbal communication skills; 
 Be able to work independently; 
 Have good interpersonal skills; 
 Possess a keen attention to detail; 
 Be proficient in Microsoft Office suite. 
 
 If you consider yourself suitable for this exciting opportunity, please send us a cover letter, academic record and resume to   michelle@rebuslegal.com.au   
 Should you have any queries please call the Practice Manager -  Michelle Corbett  on  0450 477 670

This position is ideally suited to a law graduate who is looking to complete their 75 days’ work experience on a volunteer basis. The ideal candidate will have a strong academic background and a confident disposition. Excellent communication skills are essential for this role. This position will include extensive training and mentoring from senior, experienced lawyers.  Please note this is an unpaid position.  
 If you are open-minded about this position, it will be a great opportunity for self-development, you will be in a position to see an immigration law firm develop and grow, your keenness and ability to contribute will be appreciated. You must be committed and willing to complete your internship with us as there are opportunities for employment. 
 Applicant requirements: 
 
 Law student/graduate; 
 Passionate about the law; 
 Great thinking, writing, and analytical skills. 
 outgoing; 
 Involved in social and extracurricular activities; 
 Ability to keep calm under pressure; 
 Is confident that they will be self-sufficient financially (as the position is voluntary); 
 
 Benefits: 
 
 To be part of a fun and hip team; 
 Ability to assist in business management decisions; 
 Opportunity to increase knowledge and business skills; 
 Mentorship. 
 
 Please apply with a Cover letter, CV and Academic Transcript via email to  HR@thinkvisa.com.au . 
 Please note: you must apply BY EMAIL. 
 Job Types: Full-time, Volunteer 
 Location: 
 
 Melbourne VIC (Preferred) 
 
 Work Eligibility: 
 
 The candidate can work permanently with no restriction on hours (Preferred) 
 
 Benefits: 
 
 Training and professional development assistance

Two positions are available for this Brisbane based boutique law firm specialising in property and commercial law:  
 1. PLT placement for law graduate who wish to explore in practical legal experiences/secure PLT placement; 
 2. Junior level solicitor for candidates who have basic knowledge in Conveyancing/property law area;  
 3. Mandarin/Cantonese  Speaking is a mandatory for both positions.

Vista Legal is offering a full-time solicitor role in Property Law to law graduate commence from 18 January 2022. 
 The successful candidate will possess 
 
 Mandarin speaking and writing abilities 
 Good attention to details and time management skills 
 Ability to work effectively to tight deadlines 
 Ability to relate to people at all levels and effectively work in a team 
 
 Position Description 
 
 Conduct legal research and make enquiries with relevant parties/departments etc; 
 Correspond and liaise with clients and other relevant parties; 
 Take instructions from supervisor while applying judgment to propose solutions to day-to-day problems; 
 Manage legal documents and maintain proper filing; 
 Strong written, oral and interpersonal communication skills; 
 Exhibit self-motivation and self-management; 
 A positive attitude and willingness to learn; 
 Experience with LEAP would be preferable, but not essential. 
 
 Vista Legal is committed to offering the successful applicant an opportunity to grow, learn and progress under sound mentorship and guidance.   
 Salary will be negotiated based on level of experience.

We are a boutique law firm situated in Brookvale on the Northern Beaches, specialising in commercial litigation and corporate and personal insolvency.  As a small firm, we also provide legal services in a range of areas including debt recovery, conveyancing and property law, building and construction law and wills and estates. 
 We are seeking a Graduate/Junior Lawyer who: 
 
 Is hard working and able to show initiative; 
 Is motivated and keen to learn; 
 Is committed to developing organised and efficient work practices; 
 Demonstrates an ability to work independently and as part of a team; 
 Is passionate about working within a small team; 
 Ideally has a minimum of at least 6 months experience and holds a practicing certificate; and 
 Has experience working with LEAP. 
 
 This is the perfect opportunity to live and work locally in a friendly and relaxed environment whilst being offered the opportunity to be immersed in challenging and interesting work.  Experience is not necessary, however, your desire and attitude to learn and show initiative is key. 
 To apply for this role, please forward your cover letter and resume to info@mcleanlaw.net.au.

We are a general law practice located in Sydney CBD practising in the area of property law, conveyancing, commercial litigation, wills and estate and family law. 
 We are seeking a property lawyer or licenced conveyancer with no less than 2 years post admission experience.   
 The successful candidate will: 
 
 be familiar with conveyancing (both established and off the plan property), leasing and purchase/sale of business; 
 be proficient in PEXA and Leap; 
 be able to work autonomously and manage their own files with minimum supervision; 
 have exceptional time management and client management skills. 
 
 Chinese language skill (Mandarin/Cantonese) is highly regarded but not essential.  
 Remuneration will be commensurate with the experience.  
 Please send the application with a current CV and academic transcript to  davis@summitlegal.com.au

Our long established (1970) and well-respected general law practice (areas of law include Conveyancing, Leasing, Wills & Probate, Estate Planning, Family Provision, Family Law, Commercial, Debt Recovery, General Civil Litigation, and Criminal) located at Dee Why  in the Northern Beaches of Sydney is currently recruiting PLT Work Experience Placements for 2021/2022  on an ongoing basis.  Starting dates will vary.  Working a minimum of 2-3 days per week on a voluntary unpaid basis. 
 Placements will be exposed to many aspects of a general suburban law practice including (depending on the Placement’s individual aptitude and skills): 
 
 Legal research, analysis, problem solving, and assisting with client advising; 
 File management, including electronic storage/archiving, inputting and maintaining accurate client information and communications; 
 Transactional and litigation document preparation; 
 Client communications and liaison, including answering enquiries and taking initial instructions; 
 Occasional court representation in interlocutory listings (with leave of the relevant court) and instructing/attending on Counsel/Principals at court; 
 General support for our senior lawyers (including our Managing Principal who was formerly a senior Barrister at the NSW Bar); and 
 Occasionally assisting the Duty Lawyers at the local Northern Beaches Community Legal Centre. 
 
  We are looking for law graduates who:  
 
 are highly intelligent and motivated self-starters; 
 demonstrate good initiative and judgement and, above all, common sense; 
 are keen to learn; and 
 have above-average computer skills and academic grades. 
 
 Applications will be considered on a rolling basis and should be sent by email attaching (in Word or pdf) a 1 page cover letter and a CV/Resume document.  Please ensure your cover letter includes your available start date, your preferred days, and how many days placement you can commit to, as well as your availability for interview if you are short-listed. 
 Applications should be emailed to  Ms   Esther Locker  at   ecl@stlegal.com.au   including “PLT Work Experience Placement Application” in the email subject line.
